		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">We intend to investigate the structure of the congruence kernel of an arithmetic lattice in a rank one semisimple algebraic group over a local field.  (These kernels have been shown to be infinite by Lubotzky).A number of structural results are known for the (infinite) congruence kernels of SL2 over an arithmetic dedekind domain with finitely many units, due to Lubotzky, Mel'Nikov, Zalesskii and the principal investigator.  We intend to extend these to congruence kernels of the above type, using a decomposition theorem of Lubotzky for subgroups of these lattices, together with method, due to the principal investigator, involving the closure in the congruence topology of a subgroup of such a lattice.For the case where the local field has non-zero characteristic we intend to extend a decomposition theorem of Zalesskkii for the congruence kernel of SL2 over a coordinate ring of arithmetic type.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
